profile_positions.description:
PhD dissertation research on the impact of international trade policy on the geographic location of manufacturing activities and regional productivity growth patterns within countries;

Conducted a study of vertical coordination strategies among US organic produce supply chain operators and a study of US Mid-east and Southeast wineries’ marketing strategies as part of a rural economic diversification programme;

Teaching Assistant and guest instructor for an upper-level undergraduate course on market dynamics and firm strategy in the food industry (fall 2007).
